The paper discusses the use of reinforcement learning for automatic testing and falsification of cyberphysical systems, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The specific focus on autonomous vehicles, robots, and airplanes suggests that the paper may also fall under the categories of robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY). The use of Signal Temporal Logic to model dynamic constraints suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) or software engineering (cs.SE).
